+----------------------% Tutorial for Xerox 2700 +----------------------
%Selection ===>_ZCMD
+
+  The Xerox 2700/3700 is a remote printer designed to print small quant
+  of output.  Output limits are established for each printer so you wil
+  to check the output limits with your local Xerox coordinator.
+
+  Entering%?+for the %Font Selection+will present you with a display of
+  all available fonts for your Xerox 2700 or 3700.  The following fonts
+  are available on all of the Xerox 2700/3700 printers:
+
+ Font Name       LPI   Type       Cols  Lines  Comments
+ XCP14-L        8.57   Landscape   132   66     *Default
+ Titan10iso-P   6      Portrait     70   58     *Letter Titan
+
+The following topics are presented in sequence, or may be selected by n
+
+ %1+ Margin Specifications
+ %2+ Margin and Tab Conversion Table
+ %3+ Error Codes on the Xerox 2700
+ %4+ Xerox 2700 Command Reference Summary
)PROC
     &ZSEL = TRANS( &ZCMD
                1,TX2700A
                2,TX2700B
                3,TX2700C
                4,TX2700D
                *,'?'
                )
    &CONT = TX2700A
)END
